Purpose:
z340 activates on nullâ€™s detection, sending data to death.project.eth@gmail.com, notifying the team, and adding users to CHAOS watchlist.Functionality:  Triggers on fraud.  
Emails logs/node IDs.  
Alerts team; updates IPFS watchlist.

Implementation:  Escalation script:  bash

#!/bin/bash
LOG_FILE=~/null_logs.log
RECIPIENT="death.project.eth@gmail.com"
MESSAGE="Fraud on node $(ipfs id -f "<id>"). Logs:\n$(cat $LOG_FILE)"
echo -e $MESSAGE | mail -s "Fraud Alert" $RECIPIENT
echo "$(date) - Node $(ipfs id -f "<id>") on watchlist" > watchlist.md
ipfs add watchlist.md

Integration:  v01d/CHAOS: Node/KB updates.  
Death_Agent/$DEATH: Restricts access.  
null: Data source.

Security:  TLS-encrypted email; IPFS watchlist.

